    <string name="settings_help_account">Account: sign in/out, cloud sync, and data transfer. This section stores backup, import/export, and manual sync options so your settings and sources stay aligned across devices.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_ai_processing">AI processing: summary logic, limits, deduplication, length rules, and filters. This section affects both quality and speed, and controls how much content AI analyzes.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_api_keys">API keys: connect AI providers and choose models for summary and embedding tasks. Add keys here, control which ones are active, and verify model availability.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_recommendations">Recommendations: configure topic subscriptions and related personalization scenarios. It helps you enable relevant themes quickly without manually searching for every source.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_feed">Feed: how news is displayed in the feed, including media, descriptions, item count, and card behavior. It affects how compact or detailed everyday reading feels.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_scheduled">Scheduled summaries: auto-generation time, push notifications, and regular run settings. Use it to receive summaries automatically at the chosen time.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_general">General: app language, summary language, theme, and other global settings. This is the baseline interface behavior applied across the app.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_memory">Memory: service actions for local data, such as clearing, resetting, and storage maintenance. Use carefully, because some actions remove cache or accumulated history.</string>
    <string name="summary_prompt_default">Task: structure the feed or scheduled digest into key themes, select the most important stories in each theme, write short distinct headlines, and attach each story to the best supporting source.</string>
